      "writtenOn": "2021-07-09T21:21:52Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is feasible: we could monitor the emulator processes with `ps aux` every 1 second or so after sending SIGTERM from emulators.StopAllEmulators(), and return when all processes are finished. Maybe kill them with SIGKILL after N seconds if they don\u0027t die with SIGTERM.\n\nThat said, I think it would be OK to just kill them with SIGKILL. Honestly I don\u0027t think graceful termination buys us much. We could do this via a new emulators.ForceStopAllEmulators() method.\n\nWhich option do you prefer?",
      "parentUuid": "bb05a16b_2d8d4de1",
